p>

Mastering the art of stying hair extensions isn’t as hard as it may appear, all it takes is a bit of practice. Today, we are giving you five hacks for styling your hair extensions to turn your styles from ordinary to extraordinary. <p> </p>

Here are some of the best hacks when it comes to hair extension styling. These tips will make your styling so much easier, save you a bunch of time and make your extensions last a ton longer. If you want all of this then keep reading.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-23c5" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jNHqnW kXSKNz pf-24_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-cqJhZP gRKDwp"><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-25_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-26_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-27_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-29_">1: Use the right tools</span></h3></div></div></div><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-30_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-31_"><div title="Styling Brunette Hair Extensions" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-32_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-458ae18b--how-to-style-extensions_1200x.png?v=1597335543" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-458ae18b--how-to-style-extensions.png?v=1597335543 1536w" width="800" height="800" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Hair Extensions top tips" title="Styling Brunette Hair Extensions"/></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-33_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-34_"><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-35_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-37_">Using the wrong tools on your <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/" target="_blank">hair extensions</a>&nbsp;will make styling so much harder and jeopardise the quality of the hair. This may seem far-fetched but even the hairbrush you use is important. Investing in the right tools will help your extensions last so much longer and is totally worth it. <p> </p>Make sure you use a detangling brush, or a wide tooth comb to <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/brush-hour-the-ultimate-guide-to-hairbrush-types" target="_blank">brush your hair</a>. Also ensure you are using products designed for hair extensions on your hair. Doing these simple things will prolong the quality and duration of your hair extensions.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-38_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-40_">2: Non-slip technique</span></h3><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-41_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-43_">If you have second-day hair or have been wearing your extensions for a long period of time, you may have trouble with your hair extensions slipping. This may also be the case if your hair is a bit thinner. The trick is to add some hold to your hair before you <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/collections/clip-in-hair-extensions" target="_blank">clip your extensions</a> in, divide your hair and tease the roots for extra hold.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-0012" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jNHqnW kXSKNz pf-44_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-cqJhZP gRKDwp"><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-45_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-46_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-47_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-49_">3: Use your hanger to the best of its ability</span></h3><div title="Hair Extensions hacks" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-50_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-8ae18be3--clipinhairextensions5hacksnumber3_1200x.png?v=1597335720" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-8ae18be3--clipinhairextensions5hacksnumber3.png?v=1597335720 1536w" width="577" height="576" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Hanging Hair Extensions" title="Hair Extensions hacks"/></div><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-51_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-53_">Hangers are great for keeping your hair more luscious for longer, they help to keep your hair nice and tangle free. That is not the only benefit of using hair extension hangers. Styling is always difficult at the back of your head whether it’s your natural hair or extensions. To make it easier, style your hair extensions whilst they are still hung up. You will get the look you want and save a lot of time.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-54_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-56_">4: Upside down hair extensions</span></h3></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-57_"><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-58_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-60_">We know hot crazy the idea of wearing your extensions upside down is. however, when you are creating an updo, whether it is a <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/5-killer-hairstyles-with-a-clip-in-ponytail-and-how-to-slay-them" target="_blank">ponytail </a>or an intricate bun, things are a little different. <p> </p>When you have your extension in the normal way and trying to create these styles, it can be a little bit harder to conceal the seams. The trick is to place your extensions in, upside down from the nape of your neck to your ears. This will make blending in your hair extensions so much easier. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-61_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-63_">5: Tones and layers</span></h3><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-64_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-66_">When you are trying to create different tones of the same colour, i.e darker and mid-toned brunette, then layering is the best way to make this seem more natural. This look has been gaining a lot of attention recently due to the increasing popularity of balayage. <p> </p>To create this with hair extensions, make sure you clip them in horizontally to create layers that will match your hair cut.</span></p><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-67_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-69_">Will you try these tricks with your hair extensions? Let us know Let us know, and&nbsp; don't forget to hashtag&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.instagram.com/explore/tags/wearcliphair/">#WearCliphair</a></span> on <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.instagram.com/cliphairlimited/">Instagram,</a> <a href="https://web.facebook.com/Cliphair.Limited">Facebook</a></span> or <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://twitter.com/Cliphairlimited">Twitter</a></span> to show off your hair extensions looks!<p> </p></span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-70_"><div data-slider="{'slidesToShow':{'all':3,'laptop':3,'tablet':2,'mobile':1},'slidesToScroll':{'all':1,'laptop':1,'tablet':1,'mobile':1},'loop':false,'autoPlay':false,'autoPlayDelay':3000,'pauseOnHover':false,'id':'4605fee9-bd75-4b5c-8de3-29c477001298'}" class="sc-hiCibw dJQIUB pf-71_ glider-n-1" style="visibility:hidden;height:369px" data-pf-type="Slider"><div class="glider" style="--g-xs:0px"><div class